## Mandatory QA Checklist

Before answering, validate:

- canonical periods declared first
- frozen scoring definition declared before the per-dimension loop
- every successful dimension uses the same frozen scoring definition
- no dimension-specific scoring simplification was introduced
- every field uses correct period alias
- every filtered additive component wrapped in `coalesce(..., 0)`
- ratios recomputed from null-safe additive components
- no unexpected null additive values remain
- same `r` reused across all analyzed dimensions
- every candidate dimension accounted for in inventory
- every eligible dimension ranked in prioritization table
- explicit user confirmation obtained
- every confirmed analyzed dimension is marked as either `done` or `failed`
- every successful confirmed analyzed dimension has a valid normalized scored table
- all successful normalized scored tables share exact schema
- appended cross-dimension significance table exists when at least one dimension succeeds
- final ranking derived from appended table only
- dimension-level QA note exists for every confirmed analyzed dimension
- every failed dimension has a recorded failure reason
- failed dimensions were not rescued by changing the scoring logic

If any check fails:
- regenerate or return `INCOMPLETE`

